4. Monetization & Go-To-Market (GTM) Strategy
The "À La Carte" SaaS + Ticketing Model
"Basics" Tier (The Wedge): Free or nominal monthly fee ($29/mo) + Transaction Fee (e.g., $1.50 + 2.5% per ticket). Includes Phase 1 core (Ticketing, Waivers, QR Kiosk Check-in, Rostering).
"Basics+" Tier: $149-$299/mo + Ticket Fees. Unlocks Phase 2 features (Series linking, Rule Authoring, Global Artifacts).
"Whole Ecosystem": $499+/mo or Enterprise + Ticket Fees. Unlocks Phase 3 Live Game Engine.
À La Carte Add-ons: Bulk SMS text credits, extra cloud storage, physical QR-scanning kiosk rentals.
Contextual Commerce (The VC Multiplier)
Packing List Affiliates: Producers set mandatory gear sheets in-app. IBIS dynamically links required items to major retailers (Evike, Airsoft GI) using native affiliate links. IBIS takes a 5-8% cut.
In-Game Sponsorships (Phase 3): Gear vendors sponsor digital map assets (e.g., "KWA Armory Control Zone").
Targeted Vendor Leads: Post-AAR, highly segmented email offers based on a player's exact in-game role (Sniper, Support).
5. The Phased Product Roadmap
Phase 1: "Unified Command" MVP (Operations & Context)
Focus: Owning the pre-game lifecycle, ticketing, and player rostering.
Event Container: Greenfield event creation (dates, locations, schedule, context).
Ticketing & Monetization: Stripe-integrated ticket sales tied to specific event containers.
Waivers & Kiosk Check-In: Digital pre-check, distributed waivers, and rapid "one-click" QR scanner kiosks for on-site staff.
Packing Lists & Commerce: Producers set mandatory gear, linked directly to affiliate retail partners.
Hierarchical Rostering: Faction creation (logos, uniforms, lore) and automated/manual assignment of players into Factions -> Platoons -> Squads.
Role-Based Dashboards: Producer task readiness, Staff roster oversight, Player utility/pre-check status.
Strictly Scoped Comms: Persistent text chat automatically generated based on roster hierarchy (Faction, Squad) and core push/email notifications.
Phase 2: The SaaS Moat & VC Scale (Franchising)
Focus: Enterprise-grade platform features to lock in high-LTV producers.
Event Series & Narrative: Connecting multiple events to build cohesive storylines based on gameplay outcomes.
Templating Engine: Rapid deployment of game modes or whole events based on past successes.
Global Artifact & Asset Management: Permission-tagged rules, maps, and briefings with deep external drive linking (Google Workspace, OneDrive).
Rule Authoring Engine: Native, syncable document creation.
Automated Post-Event AARs: System-consolidated surveys and data categorization.
Phase 3: The Live-Action Game Engine (Geospatial Mechanics)
Focus: The "Power Fantasy" – turning physical airsoft into a tech-facilitated video game.
The Tactical Grid: Editable geo-maps, geofencing (boundaries/safe zones), and low-latency live geolocation for staff.
Map-to-Schedule Sync: Objectives trigger automatically based on the Phase 1 schedule.
Dynamic Respawn Logic: Anti-camping routing, squad grouping, and player-placed respawns.
Objectives & Minigames: Capture points, QR-based data hacks, HVT eliminations, and resource retrieval.
Environmental Hazards: Rad zones, out-of-bounds death timers, and UI-activated protective equipment.
The "Active" Run-Time Mode: Live command center for staff to push immediate overrides and schedule shifts.
Phase 4: The Cognitive Battlefield (AI Integration)
Focus: Leveraging LLMs to reduce cognitive load and create dynamic scenarios.
AI Pre-Game Support Agent: LLM trained on Phase 2 artifacts to auto-answer player questions.
Dynamic Balancing: AI monitors Phase 3 geospatial data to detect "steamrolling" and suggests real-time map adjustments to staff.
Generative Storyboarding: AI assists producers by generating narrative briefing scripts or suggesting objective placements.
Synthesized AARs: AI ingests post-game surveys, chat logs, and map data to write comprehensive executive summaries.
6. Phase 1 UX/UI Constraints & Guardrails
Designers must adhere strictly to these physical and environmental realities:
The "Tactical Glove" Rule: Buttons, sliders, and navigation elements must be massive. No tiny text links.
The "High-Noon Glare" Rule: Mobile UI will be used in direct sunlight. High contrast is mandatory.
The "Spotty Cell Tower" Rule: The player's Check-In QR code must be accessible offline (cached locally or Apple/Google Wallet). The staff iPad scanner must queue offline scans and sync when reconnected.
The Cognitive Load Limit: Use progressive disclosure. Only show the user the exact next step they need to take.
7. Phase 1 Engineering & Database Architecture
Core Epics
Epic 1: The Event Container, Commerce, & Ticketing: Create the centralized event page, Stripe sync, and affiliate Packing List integration.
Epic 2: Frictionless Check-In & Waivers: Build the Pre-Check Dashboard, the high-contrast Player QR Screen, and the rapid-fire Staff Scanner Kiosk (<3 seconds per scan).
Epic 3: Hierarchical Rostering: Build the Faction Builder, the drag-and-drop Roster Matrix, and the Player Roster View.
Epic 4: Scoped Comms & Role-Based Dashboards: Build role-specific home screens and hierarchical chat channels (no manual group creation allowed in V1).
Core Database Schema (Supabase/PostgreSQL)
Use UUIDs for primary keys. Enforce strict Foreign Key constraints.
users: id, email, legal_name, callsign, phone, global_role
events: id, producer_id, title, location_name, start_date, end_date, status
ticket_tiers: id, event_id, name, price, inventory_count
packing_lists: id, event_id, item_name, is_mandatory, affiliate_url
registrations: id (QR generator), event_id, user_id, ticket_tier_id, waiver_signed, payment_status, check_in_status, check_in_time
factions: id, event_id, name, commander_id
platoons: id, faction_id, name
squads: id, platoon_id, name, squad_leader_id
roster_assignments: id, registration_id (Unique), squad_id, event_role
chat_channels: id, event_id, target_type, target_id (Polymorphic)
messages: id, channel_id, sender_id, content, created_at
Supabase Row Level Security (RLS) Policies
Enable RLS on all tables to enforce the "Fog of War" and protect PII.
-- EVENTS & COMMERCE (The Producer's Lock)
CREATE POLICY "Public events are viewable by everyone" ON events FOR SELECT USING (status = 'published' OR status = 'active');
CREATE POLICY "Producers can update their own events" ON events FOR ALL USING (auth.uid() = producer_id);
CREATE POLICY "Ticket tiers are viewable by everyone" ON ticket_tiers FOR SELECT USING (true);
CREATE POLICY "Producers manage their event tiers" ON ticket_tiers FOR ALL USING (
  EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM events WHERE events.id = ticket_tiers.event_id AND events.producer_id = auth.uid())
);

-- REGISTRATIONS (The Privacy Shield)
CREATE POLICY "Players can view their own registrations" ON registrations FOR SELECT USING (auth.uid() = user_id);
CREATE POLICY "Producers can manage event registrations" ON registrations FOR ALL USING (
  EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM events WHERE events.id = registrations.event_id AND events.producer_id = auth.uid())
);

-- ROSTER ASSIGNMENTS (The Fog of War)
CREATE POLICY "Players see their faction roster" ON roster_assignments FOR SELECT USING (
  squad_id IN (
    SELECT s.id FROM squads s JOIN platoons p ON s.platoon_id = p.id WHERE p.faction_id = (
      SELECT p2.faction_id FROM roster_assignments ra2 JOIN squads s2 ON ra2.squad_id = s2.id JOIN platoons p2 ON s2.platoon_id = p2.id WHERE ra2.registration_id IN (SELECT id FROM registrations WHERE user_id = auth.uid())
    )
  )
);

-- CHAT MESSAGES (The Fog of War)
CREATE POLICY "Players can only access their assigned comms" ON messages FOR ALL USING (
  EXISTS (
    SELECT 1 FROM chat_channels cc WHERE cc.id = messages.channel_id AND (
      cc.target_id IN (
        SELECT s.id FROM roster_assignments ra JOIN squads s ON ra.squad_id = s.id WHERE ra.registration_id IN (SELECT id FROM registrations WHERE user_id = auth.uid())
        UNION
        SELECT p.id FROM roster_assignments ra JOIN squads s ON ra.squad_id = s.id JOIN platoons p ON s.platoon_id = p.id WHERE ra.registration_id IN (SELECT id FROM registrations WHERE user_id = auth.uid())
        UNION
        SELECT f.id FROM roster_assignments ra JOIN squads s ON ra.squad_id = s.id JOIN platoons p ON s.platoon_id = p.id JOIN factions f ON p.faction_id = f.id WHERE ra.registration_id IN (SELECT id FROM registrations WHERE user_id = auth.uid())
      )
    )
  )
);
